verses.roman:
ācārya-gosāñi prabhuke kahe ṭhāre-ṭhore
ācārya tarjā paḍe, keha bujhite nā pāre

synonyms: ācārya-gosāñi—Advaita Ācārya; prabhuke—unto Śrī Caitanya Mahāprabhu; kahe—speaks; ṭhāre-ṭhore—by indications; ācārya—Advaita Ācārya; tarjā paḍe—reads some poetic passages; keha—anyone; bujhite—to understand; nā pāre—was not able.
translation: Then Śrīla Advaita Ācārya said something to Caitanya Mahāprabhu through gestures and read some poetic passages, which no one understood.
